üö´ NO 'any' TYPE ALLOWED:
This project enforces STRICT TYPE CHECKING.

The 'any' type is BANNED. You must use explicit types.

‚ùå NEVER use:
  - ': any'
  - '<any>'
  - 'any[]'
  - 'as any'
  - 'Record<string, any>'

‚úÖ ALWAYS use specific types:
  - For unknowns: 'unknown' + type guards
  - For objects: 'Record<string, TypeHere>'
  - For generics: '<T extends SomeType>'
  - For JSON: Create a proper type/class

Example:
```typescript
// ‚ùå BAD
function process(data: any): any {
  return data;
}

// ‚úÖ GOOD
function process<T extends Record<string, unknown>>(data: T): T {
  return data;
}

// ‚úÖ GOOD with type guard
function process(data: unknown): ProcessedData {
  if (!isValidData(data)) {
    throw new Error('Invalid data');
  }
  return processInternal(data);
}
```

See: .claude/rules/strict-typing-class-patterns.md
